<p>July 1915</p>
<p>Thursday 22</p>
<p>Vaccinated this morning.</p>
<p>Granted home leave for four days.</p>
<p>No pay &amp; no pennies so not much chance of getting to Grafton.</p>
<p>Wired return for 30/- &amp; walked around with Francis.</p>
<p>He met his friends so I was left.</p>
<p>Saw Curry, Kenney, Miss Jepson &amp; Mrs. Bruce</p>
<p>Went to Soldiers Club in evening &amp; wrote a lot of letters.</p>
<p>No word from Rita yet.</p>
